<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="774" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1190: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lauchlin Currie</persName>,
                                Administrative Assistant to President
                                <persName>Roosevelt</persName>, to Madame <persName type="to">Chiang
                                    Kai-shek</persName>
                            </hi><note n="10" xml:id="d774fn1">Copy received in the Department on
                                October 17.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-16">October 16, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Shipping 285 anti-aircraft 50-caliber guns. No more available at present
                            owing to necessity of arming all our merchant ships. Hope for more
                            later. Authority has been granted for you to hire 200 more pilots
                            here.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>